============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

Theorem/Law:  Golden Ratio
Branch:       Geometry
Formula:      phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2 = 1.618...
Applications: Art, architecture, nature, design
Discoverer:   Ancient Greeks (500)

Theorem/Law:  Central Limit Theorem
Branch:       Statistics
Formula:      Sample means approach normal distribution
Applications: Polling, quality control, finance
Discoverer:   Lyapunov (1901)

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Plato's Theory of Forms
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Physical objects are imperfect copies of eternal abstract Forms
Philosopher:  Plato
Example:      The perfect circle exists only as a Form; drawn circles approximate it

Concept:      Categorical Imperative
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Act only on principles you could will to be universal laws
Philosopher:  Immanuel Kant
Example:      Don't lie; if universal lying existed, language would break down

Concept:      Determinism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   All events are causally determined by prior events and natural laws
Philosopher:  Laplace/Spinoza
Example:      If universe were rewound exactly, every event would repeat identically

============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Market Failure
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Free markets fail to allocate resources efficiently
Formula:    Social cost = private + external cost
Economist:  Arthur Pigou
Example:    Carbon emissions: negative externality requiring government intervention

Concept:    Compound Interest
Category:   Finance
Definition: Interest calculated on initial principal and accumulated interest
Formula:    A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt)
Economist:  Various
Example:    Einstein allegedly called it the 8th wonder of the world

Concept:    Supply and Demand
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Price determined where quantity supplied equals demanded
Formula:    P* where Qd=Qs
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Housing prices rise when population grows but supply stays fixed

